WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:00.066 --> 00:00:02.950
Runeshapes, inscriptions.

00:00:02.950 --> 00:00:05.800
These are my life's work.

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:08.350
The more I studied,
the more I began to see

00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:11.350
similar shapes in the stars above.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.350
It was then that I dedicated myself
to becoming

00:00:15.916 --> 00:00:17.233
a Runeseeker.

00:00:18.550 --> 00:00:23.150
As Farrow so kindly explained, runes are
very powerful and ancient inscriptions,

00:00:23.150 --> 00:00:26.350
and they can be socketed into your items
to grant them more power.

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:30.300
During the league, inscribing symbols
into remnants will let you choose between

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:33.983
a bunch of different crafting runes
that you can use to enhance your items.

00:00:34.633 --> 00:00:38.183
When you come across a remnant,
it has a number of slots ranging from two

00:00:38.733 --> 00:00:39.866
to seven.

00:00:39.866 --> 00:00:42.783
The more slots,
the more powerful the remnant encounter,

00:00:42.783 --> 00:00:45.450
but the more options
you'll have to choose between.

00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:47.333
At the start of the game,
you might find yourself

00:00:47.333 --> 00:00:49.400
crafting simple damage or resistance runes

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:51.116
that are available at a lower level

00:00:51.116 --> 00:00:52.616
than you would normally be able
to get them,

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:54.433
giving you a decent power boost.

00:00:54.650 --> 00:00:56.516
But things quickly get more interesting.

00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:00.233
There are 22 runes for adding
or modifying runic ward,

00:01:00.483 --> 00:01:02.450
a new resource
that can protect you from death.

00:01:03.033 --> 00:01:06.900
Using these runes, you can add an extra
defensive layer or turn your runic ward

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:10.150
into an offensive weapon
using Kalguuran Runic Skills.

00:01:13.183 --> 00:01:16.600
There are also 13 runes that add powers
specific to weapon types,

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.833
like this one which gives a chance for
grenades to explode a second time.

00:01:21.283 --> 00:01:24.566
Or this one which gives you a new buff
called Druidic Prowess

00:01:24.616 --> 00:01:26.200
when heavy stunning enemies.

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:29.850
In addition,

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.850
there are 22 runes
designed to give you power at low levels

00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:35.850
like this one, which gives you
a bunch of elemental resistances,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.683
or this one
which gives you a ton of spirit.

00:01:38.683 --> 00:01:42.300
These runes are designed to be powerful,
but drop off in value as you level up.

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:45.300
They're great for power
leveling a second character in the league.

00:01:45.733 --> 00:01:47.933
We also have six runes
that can be used to expand

00:01:47.933 --> 00:01:51.016
the pool of modifiers used
when doing high level crafting.

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:55.133
So for example, you can socket
Katla’s Gloom into some gloves

00:01:55.133 --> 00:01:58.516
and it will enable the crafting
of a bunch of new decay modifiers

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:00.650
that can be used for
damage over time builds.

00:02:01.216 --> 00:02:03.316
After socketing one of this type of rune

00:02:03.316 --> 00:02:06.416
use regular Exalts or Chaos orbs to
try and craft the new mods.

00:02:08.666 --> 00:02:10.583
There are also several runes that have one off

00:02:10.583 --> 00:02:13.900
powerful effects on items,
but are bound forever into the socket,

00:02:14.066 --> 00:02:17.183
like this one, which allows any item
to gain another suffix.

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:23.516
Or this one,
which allows you to create a jewel socket.

00:02:29.166 --> 00:02:30.400
Or this series of runes

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.566
that can convert any elemental mod
from one element to another.

00:02:34.933 --> 00:02:37.700
There's even a rune
that can upgrade any other rune,

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:39.750
allowing you to upgrade them
beyond the normal limit.

00:02:42.133 --> 00:02:45.133
The last one I want to show you
today is Aldur’s Legacy.

00:02:45.433 --> 00:02:50.266
 A special rune that can be socketed into any Kalguuran or Ezomite Unique to destroy it,

00:02:50.266 --> 00:02:53.233
but create a new rune that takes some of the properties of the unique.

00:02:53.816 --> 00:02:54.983
So for example,

00:02:54.983 --> 00:02:58.350
use this on a Trampletoe
to create a Legacy of Trampletoe rune.

00:02:58.500 --> 00:02:59.950
Socket into any boots and,

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:01.683
just like the unique it came from,

00:03:01.683 --> 00:03:05.233
you’ll deal 10% of overkill damage
to all enemies in a two metre radius.

00:03:05.983 --> 00:03:08.700
Or how about
the Legacy of Twisted Empyrean?

00:03:08.700 --> 00:03:10.466
Destroy a Twisted Empyrean

00:03:10.466 --> 00:03:13.666
and you can add cold damage based
on your maximum mana to any weapon.

00:03:14.783 --> 00:03:17.900
With Aldur’s Legacy you can create
another hundred or so runes

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.950
with all sorts of unique effects.

00:03:22.516 --> 00:03:25.116
At this point, you might be thinking,
that's a lot of new runes

00:03:25.116 --> 00:03:26.350
and you'd be right.

00:03:26.350 --> 00:03:28.350
This is the Runes of Aldur, after all.

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:31.000
But we didn't want the old runes
to be left behind either.

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.700
A significant number of the old runes

00:03:32.700 --> 00:03:34.800
that were not being used
are being buffed as well,

00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:37.233
making this crafting system
significantly better.

00:03:37.566 --> 00:03:39.183
Explore everything runes have to offer

00:03:39.183 --> 00:03:42.883
in the Return of the Ancients update
on May 29th. See you there!

